So you can get quite a bit of file
system bandwidth if you're using

00:47:22.710 --> 00:47:26.200
this directly with an XServe RAID as
part of an XAN or anything like that.

00:47:26.200 --> 00:47:28.240
Very, very high I/O bandwidth.

00:47:28.260 --> 00:47:30.040
And of course the built-in drives.

